@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Xix" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Xix runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any shape, except on an 'X' shape, this will
make it rotate by 45 degrees. If it connects diagonally with other
shapes and the resulting series of 3 connected shapes include at
least one 'X' shape, all three shapes will be removed from the
board and you will get points according to whether or not all 3
shapes are of the same colour and if there is one or two 'X'
shapes...

  Scoring goes like this:

-3 shapes of different colours including one 'X' shape: 1 point
-3 shapes of same colour including one 'X' shape:       5 points
-3 shapes of different colours including 2 'X' shapes:  20 points
-3 shapes of same colour including 2 'X' shapes:        100 points

  When a series of 3 connected has been removed from the game
board, they will be replaced by new coloured shapes.

  Note that the game only analyze the first series of connected
shapes that it finds. So if there are more than one series of
connected shapes, whether they include 'X' shapes or not, the other
series will be ignored...

  The game continues until there are no 'X' shape on the board.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

